This paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically packing triangles in interval graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational geometry, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorics, which is covered in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with graph theory and optimization, which are covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
